HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 379
BY REPRESENTATIVES PHELPS AND TURNER
A RESOLUTION
To commend Louisiana Department of Education 2026 High School Student of the Year
Melissa An Le.
WHEREAS, the Louisiana Department of Education (LDOE) honored twenty-four
regional finalists and named three Louisiana Students of the Year during a ceremony at The
Cook Hotel and Conference Center in Baton Rouge; and
WHEREAS, each year, the LDOE and the Louisiana Board of Elementary and
Secondary Education (BESE) recognize students who exemplify academic excellence,
leadership, and service; finalists include one fifth, eighth, and twelfth grader from each of
the state's eight BESE regions; and
WHEREAS, the 2026 overall honorees are Sanil Savita Thorat, Kaejha Mary-Anne
Christine Stewart, and Melissa An Le; and
WHEREAS, Melissa An Le is the Louisiana High School Student of the Year; she
attends Ruston High School in Lincoln Parish and was previously named Louisiana Middle
School Student of the Year; she is an AP Scholar with Distinction and a National Merit
Commended Scholar; she served as student body president, was elected state secretary of
Future Business Leaders of America, and earned all-state recognition in speech and debate;
she advocates for expanded access to science, technology, engineering, and math education
through speaking engagements and national initiatives and has reached thousands through
her "STEM to Bloom" video series; she also serves on the National Girls Collaborative
Project board; and
WHEREAS, Melissa An Le is most deserving of recognition for bringing great pride
to Lincoln Parish and the state of Louisiana through her outstanding achievements.
